textDisplay:
I really liked the video. I honestly did. But…as a New Yorker…this is kinda…”weird”.
When you go apartment hunting, the sweet spot is to make at least 60 to 70 grand a year. If you make 20 or a little less than 40 grand, your living check to check. Of course being responsible and saving is important so that is pretty obvious.

Anyway these apartments are a bit “odd”.
Most apartments that are “cheap”are in “bad neighborhoods” or the land lords are “sketchy”. Also alot of people rent out a space in their house which is fine, but one of my friends was living in a space and I couldn’t figure out how they were affording it. Not that it was anything special, in fact it was only a tiny two room space and a bathroom. Long story short the “apartment” was not a legal dwelling and did not conform to the local renting and blah blah blah requirements. So how could she afford it working medium wage? It was illegal that’s why. So alot of it was hush hush. They could have gotten into alot of trouble with fines and what not.😂

Anyway I actually really liked the apartments, honestly, and I like the channel, but there’s a-lot to consider is all I’m saying. Plus rent usually includes nothing. It’s 3 grand a month but you still need to pay for alot of stuff that isn’t included in the rent. Plus the deposit and blah blah blah.

Lastly when I was looking for apartments, since I moved to a new state, the rent on some of them were 700 to 800 on the low end. Which about 700 to 865 or whatever living space. Multiple rooms. And everything included. Laundry facilities. A gym (for some reason but still nice). A pool. Light, gas, so on and so on. A lot of good stuff. So you could get two bedrooms, a living room, two baths, alot of closet space, a balcony, a back door patio for grilling or whatever. Plus the extra stuff I mentioned.
I was reading it carefully trying to understand what was included and what wasn’t. Maybe I’m stupid. I don’t know. But the downside is that the local Economy is different. So 20 dollars an hour in New York isn’t anything special, but 20 dollars an hour in Florida or whatever state you chose can be very different.

Long story short if your making about 500 a week working in New York. Like for amazon or something. I was making around maybe 6 or 7 with over time. Save up for about 6 months and leave. 500 + 6 months equals 3 grand. 800 + 6 months equals 4,800. If your good at saving money and you don’t mind changing jobs and finding someplace a bit away from the city, than that is my advice. And of course I didn’t do detail math because I already wrote a lot so try not to yell at me lol anyway have a good day guys and good luck out there. 👍
